column3: feedbacks
I wasn't sure ow to answer the Artificial Intelligence question because there was no definition for the author's stance.

In some cases, like "should Medicare be reformed", the author is making a valid argument -- but one that has nothing to do with the "additional information".  I.e., author is arguing against an alternative that was not on the table -- not the alternative raised by the additional information.  For this particular case re Medicare, author was arguing against *expanding* it, but the proposed alternative was *privatizing* it, so I marked "I couldn't find any reasons"
Second did not have any solid stand point and "Generations" is spelled wrong.
Very interesting points of view offered here.
Interesting subjects, thank you!

On the NATO one no reference was made directly to NATO but I decided to go with a reason.;I am assuming "cabal", not "caba" is the right word in my selected Supreme Court passage.;The "should college teach French" question some responders took literally rather than answer should college teach humanities, which made it a little difficult to evaluate their responses.

grammar in the second debate question - "Police are" rather than "is" would be correct.;Argument text on third question is extremely poorly written, making it very difficult to parse an argument.;second question uses "it" as a singular gender neutral pronoun, which is quite offensive in a native english context. "they" is preferred.

I couldn't un-click the paragraph about extreme parenting the answers.  It should be " The object is to let the child lean how to be happy by experiencing and then discussing.  If the achievement of any kind makes the heart glow, that is where the child will go"

Topic 2 stance "Open office layout should not be reconsidered" was the exact opposite of the author's argument, that is why no reasons were selected.  For Topic 3 Organic food is not the expense, I believe the argument should be Organic food is not worth the expense
